{"ts":"2026-06-25T23:07:44.220Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Investigating the Journey**\n\nOkay, I'm digging into the materials. I'm trying to figure out if there's an existing section that covers the \"homepage transformation journey,\" which needs to include the Garage, or if this is a completely new element. I am looking for other mentions of the \"journey\".\n\n\n**Mapping the Operating Model**\n\nI've got the five steps – Foundry, Factory, Operate, Optimize, and Scale – clearly defined and linked. I'm focusing on aligning these with existing landing sections to avoid duplication, and each step has a description, outcome, and route link. The UI concept is an enterprise timeline with premium feel, vertical mobile layout, subtle motion and minimal clutter. I'm reviewing the existing journey section now to ensure this all fits.\n\n\n**Defining the AI Lifecycle**\n\nI'm now integrating the five-step operating model - Foundry, Factory, Operate, Optimize, and Scale. I have finalized descriptions, statuses and icons for each step. This work involves refining their core elements, including the AI lifecycle. It appears straightforward; the flow is clearly defined and consistent with other materials. I am now working on ensuring proper icon representation.\n\n\n**Refining Route Links**\n\nI'm now focusing on refining the route links for the five steps. Currently, the \"Operate\" step has `/capabilities/operations`. I need to ensure the system is optimally linking. I have checked each link for consistency and found that \"Operate\" might ideally use `/platforms/control-center`. I'm comparing this to other existing links.\n\n\n**Revising Operating Model Links**\n\nI'm now focusing on the \"Operate,\" \"Optimize,\" and \"Scale\" route links. \"Operate\" and \"Optimize\" will use `/platforms/control-center`.  I've confirmed that \"Scale\" currently uses `/platforms/factory`, which is correct. The next step is refining the data fields to include both a `desc` (description) and an explicit `outcome` field. I need to make sure both will be displayed.\n\n\n**Clarifying Key Outcomes**\n\nI'm now nailing down specific outcomes for each step. I've re-examined each description and outcome. I've got them sketched out for Garage (Validated Prototypes), Foundry (Enterprise-Grade Agents), Factory (Industrialized Production Runs), Operate (Stabilized Live Operations), Optimize (Maximum Performance & ROI), and Scale (Enterprise-wide Expansion). Now I'm going to look at the codebase to check if these are reflected anywhere else.\n\n\n"}}
